{{Lunisolar October}} '''October 21''' is the 21st day of month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|10月 (旧暦)|lt=Kannazuki|1=Kannazuki|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} .
== Events == * {{ill|Tenchō|ja|治承|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year（{{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1180|ja|1180|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 10|ja|11月10日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – A historic meeting took place in which brothers {{ill|Minamoto no Yoritomo|ja|源頼朝|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshiie|ja|源義経|lt=Yoshiie?|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (the text reads “実朝” but context suggests a name change) met for the first time on the banks of the Kise River in Suruga. * {{ill|Seiwa|ja|貞和|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year/{{ill|Kōkoku|ja|興国|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 6th year（{{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1345|ja|1345|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 15|ja|11月15日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – The Northern Court changed its era name from {{ill|Kangyō|ja|康永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} to {{ill|Teiwa|ja|貞和|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} . * {{ill|Kansei|ja|Kansei|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 12nd year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1800|ja|1800|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 7|ja|12月7日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Inō Tadataka|ja|Ino Tadataka|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} finished surveying Ezo and the Ōshū Kaidō and returned to Edo, presenting his draft map to the shogunate in December. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1857|ja|1857|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 7|ja|12月7日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – U.S. Consul {{ill|Townsend Harris|ja|ハリス|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} visited Edo Castle and met with {{ill|Tokugawa Iesada|ja|徳川家定|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} .
== Births == * {{ill|Genwa (Japan)|ja|元和|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1617|ja|1617|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 21|ja|11月21日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Tosa Mitsuki|ja|土佐光起|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a painter († {{ill|1691|ja|1691|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
* {{ill|Hōreki|ja|Hōreki|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 10th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1760|ja|1760|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 30|ja|11月30日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Kawaoka Seishū|ja|華岡青洲|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a physician and pioneer of anesthesia († {{ill|1835|ja|1835|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
* {{ill|Bunka (era)|ja|文化 (元号)|lt=Bunka|lt_ja=文化|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 14th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1817|ja|1817|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 1|ja|12月1日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Ono Yūgorō|ja|小野友五郎|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a mathematician († {{ill|1898|ja|1898|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
* {{ill|Kaei|ja|嘉永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1849|ja|1849|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 7|ja|12月7日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Saionji Kinmochi|ja|西園寺公望|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , who served as Prime Minister on the 12th and 14th occasions and was a genrō († {{ill|1940|ja|1940|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
* {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1871|ja|1871|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 5|ja|12月5日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Doi Bansui|ja|土井晩翠|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a poet († {{ill|1952|ja|1952|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Tenshōjingo|ja|Tenpyō神護|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year（{{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|765|ja|765|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 10|ja|11月10日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Junnin Tennō|ja|淳仁天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , the 47th emperor. * {{ill|Kanbun|ja|寛文|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 9th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1669|ja|1669|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|November 16|ja|11月16日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Shakusha In|ja|シャクシャイン|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , the Ainu chief († – as noted in the text).
