{{Lunisolar October|qq=}} 
'''October 21''' is the 21st day of month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|10月 (旧暦)|lt=October (Kannazuki)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|1=Kannazuki|qq=|12=draft}}  the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=draft}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|12=draft}}  day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|qq=|12=draft}} .

== Events ==
* {{ill|Tenchō|ja|治承|qq=|12=draft}} 4th year（{{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|1180|ja|1180|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|November 10|ja|11月10日|qq=|12=draft}} ） – A historic meeting took place in which brothers {{ill|Minamoto no Yoritomo|ja|源頼朝|qq=|12=draft}}  and {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshiie|ja|源義経|lt=Yoshiie?|qq=|12=draft}}  (the text reads “実朝” but context suggests a name change) met for the first time on the banks of the Kise River in Suruga.
* {{ill|Seiwa|ja|貞和|qq=|12=draft}} 1st year/{{ill|Kōkoku|ja|興国|qq=|12=draft}} 6th year（{{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|1345|ja|1345|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|November 15|ja|11月15日|qq=|12=draft}} ） – The Northern Court changed its era name from {{ill|Kangyō|ja|康永|qq=|12=draft}}  to {{ill|Teiwa|ja|貞和|qq=|12=draft}} .
* {{ill|Kansei|ja|Kansei|qq=|12=draft}} 12nd year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|1800|ja|1800|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|December 7|ja|12月7日|qq=|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Inō Tadataka|ja|Ino Tadataka|qq=|12=draft}}  finished surveying Ezo and the Ōshū Kaidō and returned to Edo, presenting his draft map to the shogunate in December.
* {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|qq=|12=draft}} 4th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|1857|ja|1857|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|December 7|ja|12月7日|qq=|12=draft}} ） – U.S. Consul {{ill|Townsend Harris|ja|ハリス|qq=|12=draft}}  visited Edo Castle and met with {{ill|Tokugawa Iesada|ja|徳川家定|qq=|12=draft}} .

== Births ==
* {{ill|Genwa (Japan)|ja|元和|qq=|12=draft}} 3rd year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|1617|ja|1617|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|November 21|ja|11月21日|qq=|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Tosa Mitsuki|ja|土佐光起|qq=|12=draft}} , a painter († {{ill|1691|ja|1691|qq=|12=draft}} ).

* {{ill|Hōreki|ja|Hōreki|qq=|12=draft}} 10th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|1760|ja|1760|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|November 30|ja|11月30日|qq=|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Kawaoka Seishū|ja|華岡青洲|qq=|12=draft}} , a physician and pioneer of anesthesia († {{ill|1835|ja|1835|qq=|12=draft}} ).

* {{ill|Bunka (era)|ja|文化 (元号)|lt=Bunka|lt_ja=文化|qq=|12=draft}} 14th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|1817|ja|1817|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|December 1|ja|12月1日|qq=|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Ono Yūgorō|ja|小野友五郎|qq=|12=draft}} , a mathematician († {{ill|1898|ja|1898|qq=|12=draft}} ).

* {{ill|Kaei|ja|嘉永|qq=|12=draft}} 2nd year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|1849|ja|1849|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|December 7|ja|12月7日|qq=|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Saionji Kinmochi|ja|西園寺公望|qq=|12=draft}} , who served as Prime Minister on the 12th and 14th occasions and was a genrō († {{ill|1940|ja|1940|qq=|12=draft}} ).

* {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|12=draft}} 4th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|1871|ja|1871|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|December 5|ja|12月5日|qq=|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Doi Bansui|ja|土井晩翠|qq=|12=draft}} , a poet († {{ill|1952|ja|1952|qq=|12=draft}} ).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Tenshōjingo|ja|Tenpyō神護|qq=|12=draft}} 1st year（{{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|765|ja|765|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|November 10|ja|11月10日|qq=|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Junnin Tennō|ja|淳仁天皇|qq=|12=draft}} , the 47th emperor.
* {{ill|Kanbun|ja|寛文|qq=|12=draft}} 9th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|1669|ja|1669|qq=|12=draft}}  {{ill|November 16|ja|11月16日|qq=|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Shakusha In|ja|シャクシャイン|qq=|12=draft}} , the Ainu chief († – as noted in the text).

